definitions.definition: ( transitive , intransitive , US , colloquial ) To deceive; to be deceptive .
examples: Don’t try to jive me! I know where you were last night!

definitions.definition: ( intransitive , colloquial ) To dance , originally to jive or swing music; later, to jazz , rock and roll , rhythm and blues , disco , etc.

main_definition: ( transitive , intransitive , US , colloquial ) To deceive; to be deceptive .

definitions.definition: To jibe , in the sense of to accord, to agree

main_definition: ( US ) To jibe , in the sense of to accord, to agree
